Merge fantasy data

Source: R/ffl-merge.R
ffl_merge.Rd

This is a shortcut for the base merge() method that does not reorder columns or rows and returns the merged data as a tibble.

ffl_merge(x, y, ...)

Arguments

x, y

Fantasy data frames to be merged together.
...

Arguments passed to merge().

Value

A merged tibble.

Examples

team_roster(lid = 252353)
